WEBVTT

00:00.384 --> 00:05.555
<font color="#00ffff">Sync & corrections by Rafael UPD</font>
<font color="#00ffff">www.addic7ed.com/</font>

00:07.017 --> 00:11.187
[ Car horns honking,
tires screeching ]

00:11.188 --> 00:13.055
Hurry up, man. We got to get him
to the hospital.

00:13.056 --> 00:14.774
I'm going as fast
as I can!

00:14.775 --> 00:16.726
Stay with me, dad.
Stay with me.

00:16.727 --> 00:18.194
♪ And it's peaceful
in the deep ♪

00:18.195 --> 00:21.230
♪ feed you where
you cannot breathe ♪

00:21.231 --> 00:23.649
♪ no need to pray ♪

00:23.650 --> 00:27.903
♪ no need to say
"now I am under" ♪

00:27.904 --> 00:30.823
♪ and it's breaking over me ♪
[ Horn blares ]

00:30.824 --> 00:32.708
Just put the siren on!

00:32.709 --> 00:34.109
I-I've never been
in a cop car before.

00:34.110 --> 00:35.244
I don't know
where the siren is.

00:35.245 --> 00:38.080
[ Weakly ]
It's the switch in the middle.

00:38.081 --> 00:39.956
[ Siren wailing ]

00:39.957 --> 00:43.043
You're gonna be okay.
You're gonna be okay, dad.

00:43.044 --> 00:45.388
He killed Keith!
He shot him!

00:45.389 --> 00:46.756
[ Spits ]

00:46.757 --> 00:49.725
♪...are carrying me ♪

00:49.726 --> 00:51.427
♪ and all this devotion... ♪

00:51.428 --> 00:53.729
[ Siren wails ]

00:53.730 --> 00:56.148
♪...was rushing over me ♪

00:56.149 --> 00:59.435
Do you have anything <i>else
to add?</i>

00:59.436 --> 01:01.136
Yeah, make sure
you include the part

01:01.137 --> 01:02.988
where I <i>told</i> you
he was gonna attack me again

01:02.989 --> 01:04.473
and you didn't
believe me.

01:04.474 --> 01:06.308
Julian:
This is Julian Baker.

01:06.309 --> 01:07.610
I have Dan and Nathan Scott,

01:07.611 --> 01:09.745
and we're coming to
the hospital, so be ready.

01:09.746 --> 01:14.166
♪ Though the pressure's
hard to take ♪

01:14.167 --> 01:17.503
♪ it's the only way
I can escape ♪

01:17.504 --> 01:22.157
♪ it seems a heavy choice to
make ♪ [ Tires screeching ]

01:22.158 --> 01:24.326
♪ Now I am under ♪

01:24.327 --> 01:25.795
We're here.
We're here, dad!

01:25.796 --> 01:27.179
Dad?

01:27.180 --> 01:31.091
♪ A thousand Miles
onto the sea bed ♪

01:31.092 --> 01:34.670
♪ I found the place
to rest my head ♪

01:34.671 --> 01:37.139
♪ never let me go ♪

01:37.140 --> 01:38.441
He's not waking up.

01:38.442 --> 01:40.342
Come on, dad.
Come on!

01:40.343 --> 01:46.315
♪ And the arms of the ocean
are carrying me ♪

01:46.316 --> 01:52.315
♪ and all this devotion
was rushing over me ♪

01:52.489 --> 01:56.024
♪ and the question to heaven ♪

01:56.025 --> 01:58.961
♪ and it's over ♪

01:58.962 --> 02:03.623
♪ but I'm not giving in ♪

02:03.624 --> 02:06.135
Hi, hales.

02:06.136 --> 02:08.203
[ Voice breaking ]
Say that again.

02:08.204 --> 02:10.705
Hi, hales.

02:10.707 --> 02:15.010
♪ Never let me go,
never let me go ♪

02:15.011 --> 02:17.763
I can't believe
you're really here.

02:17.764 --> 02:20.048
[ Exhales sharply ]

02:20.049 --> 02:22.217
Are you okay?

02:22.218 --> 02:23.977
I am now.

02:25.000 --> 02:31.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:38.675 --> 02:40.209
Haley.

02:40.210 --> 02:42.712
It's okay.

02:42.713 --> 02:44.213
I love you.

02:44.214 --> 02:46.799
I love you, too.

02:46.800 --> 02:48.267
[ Sighs deeply ]

02:48.268 --> 02:51.053
Thank you
for coming home to me.

02:51.054 --> 02:52.855
Always.

02:52.856 --> 02:54.089
And forever.

02:54.090 --> 02:55.191
Yeah.

02:55.192 --> 02:57.193
[ Nathan sighs ]

03:07.404 --> 03:09.071
[ Doorbell rings ]

03:17.965 --> 03:20.166
I don't know what to say.

03:20.167 --> 03:22.001
You two must hate me.

03:24.171 --> 03:26.222
No.

03:26.223 --> 03:29.809
I'm sorry that I never came by
after Sara died.

03:29.810 --> 03:31.293
I always meant to.

03:31.294 --> 03:32.845
I... I just couldn't.

03:32.846 --> 03:34.764
Nah, we know, Clay.

03:34.765 --> 03:36.632
Is Logan okay?

03:36.633 --> 03:38.434
Can I see him?

03:38.435 --> 03:41.103
It might be best if he doesn't
see you for a while, son.

03:41.104 --> 03:43.372
I know that
that may seem unfair,

03:43.373 --> 03:45.908
like we're being overly
protective, but he's...

03:45.909 --> 03:47.309
He's been through so much.

03:47.310 --> 03:50.446
[ Sighs ] Um...

03:50.447 --> 03:53.449
Could you please tell him
that I came by?

03:53.450 --> 03:54.867
Of course.

03:54.868 --> 03:58.504
Thank you
for taking care of him.

04:17.608 --> 04:18.940
Oh, my God.

04:20.394 --> 04:22.445
It's not mine.

04:23.697 --> 04:25.231
Dan was shot.

04:25.232 --> 04:27.733
What?

04:29.202 --> 04:31.454
How did you know
I was here?

04:31.455 --> 04:33.289
I heard you
on the police radio.

04:33.290 --> 04:34.657
What?

04:34.658 --> 04:36.025
Don't freak out.

04:36.026 --> 04:38.193
Xavier attacked me
outside the café.

04:38.194 --> 04:40.413
What happened?
Are you okay?

04:40.414 --> 04:42.832
Yeah, I'm fine.
I'll tell you about it later.

04:42.833 --> 04:44.634
The important thing is
I'm okay,

04:44.635 --> 04:45.751
and you're okay,

04:45.752 --> 04:47.637
and he's going back to prison
for good.

04:47.638 --> 04:49.872
[ Sighs ]

04:49.873 --> 04:52.417
How's Nathan?

04:52.418 --> 04:55.811
Your blood pressure looks fine,
Mr. Scott.

04:55.812 --> 04:57.647
Thank you.
You're welcome.

04:57.648 --> 04:58.898
Thank you.

05:00.434 --> 05:03.052
All they had
was hospital vanilla.

05:03.053 --> 05:05.271
- Mmm.
- Tastes hospital-y. Oh.

05:05.272 --> 05:06.405
When we get home,

05:06.406 --> 05:09.492
I am gonna fill the freezer
with rocky road.

05:09.493 --> 05:11.110
<i>And</i> mint chocolate chip.
Mint chocolate chip.

05:11.111 --> 05:13.579
I don't want to know
what you're doing.

05:13.580 --> 05:15.081
I just want to hug Nate.

05:17.034 --> 05:18.526
Hey.
Hi!

05:19.419 --> 05:20.903
Ah, thanks for coming.

05:20.904 --> 05:23.572
You have now saved the two most
important men in my life,

05:23.573 --> 05:25.407
and I don't know how
to thank you.

05:26.677 --> 05:28.243
I'm just glad I could help.

05:28.244 --> 05:31.347
And now I can cross "steal
cop car" off my bucket list.

05:31.348 --> 05:35.718
♪ Get it wrong,
and everyone'll say ♪

05:35.719 --> 05:40.389
♪ you get a boat out just to see it
blown away ♪ [ Cellphone ringing ]

05:40.390 --> 05:43.309
♪ If you lie
and think you're okay ♪

05:43.310 --> 05:44.477
Hi, Haley.

05:44.478 --> 05:46.195
What?!

05:46.196 --> 05:47.713
They found Nathan.

05:47.714 --> 05:51.400
♪ Living on a little summer
wage ♪ [ Knock on door ]

05:51.401 --> 05:52.868
♪ Then break down... ♪

05:52.869 --> 05:55.071
Daddy,
what are you doing here?

05:55.072 --> 05:57.490
Well, after you called, I hopped
on the first plane I could.

05:57.491 --> 05:59.458
I told you and mom
I was okay.

05:59.459 --> 06:02.328
You did not have to fly
all the way out here.

06:02.329 --> 06:05.114
Of course I did.
You're my little girl.

06:05.115 --> 06:07.783
I need you safe.
Come here.

06:07.784 --> 06:10.252
Thank you.

06:10.253 --> 06:13.339
You don't have to stay here
with me the whole time.

06:13.340 --> 06:16.058
♪ I'll stay by your side ♪
are you kidding me?

06:16.059 --> 06:18.094
I'm never gonna
let you go.

06:18.095 --> 06:20.896
If I could sew my skin
to yours, I would.

06:20.897 --> 06:22.732
That's really gross.

06:22.733 --> 06:24.066
[ Both laugh ]

06:25.602 --> 06:27.970
Hey. How is he?

06:27.971 --> 06:30.406
Your father's
out of surgery.

06:30.407 --> 06:32.241
We did
everything we could,

06:32.242 --> 06:36.178
but due to the amount of blood
loss and his bad heart...

06:36.179 --> 06:37.363
It wasn't enough.

06:37.364 --> 06:39.699
All we can do now
is keep him comfortable.

06:39.700 --> 06:42.618
So my dad's gonna die?

06:42.619 --> 06:44.286
Dad!

06:44.287 --> 06:45.988
Hey. Buddy.

06:45.989 --> 06:48.323
It's good to see you.

06:48.324 --> 06:49.925
♪...Till the storm
is through ♪

06:49.926 --> 06:51.377
♪ I'll stay... ♪

06:51.378 --> 06:55.097
I'm so happy
everybody's safe.

06:55.098 --> 06:56.132
Mm.

06:56.133 --> 06:58.601
Yeah.

06:58.602 --> 06:59.769
Me too.

06:59.770 --> 07:02.388
♪ I'll stay by your side ♪

07:02.389 --> 07:04.440
♪ till the storm is through ♪

07:21.007 --> 07:23.758
Hey, kiddo.

07:23.759 --> 07:25.493
I'm glad you're back.

07:25.494 --> 07:29.965
Did you have a good time with
uncle Lucas and aunt Peyton?

07:29.966 --> 07:31.666
Yeah.

07:31.667 --> 07:33.969
It was good seeing them,
but...

07:33.970 --> 07:37.189
But they kept giving me the look
you're giving me right now.

07:37.190 --> 07:40.475
What look?

07:40.476 --> 07:42.777
The look you gave me
when you told me about Quentin,

07:42.778 --> 07:45.230
the look dad gave me when he
told me about grandma Lydia,

07:45.231 --> 07:46.698
and the look
everyone gives me

07:46.699 --> 07:49.135
when something's wrong but they
don't want to talk about it.

07:49.136 --> 07:50.986
Wow.

07:50.987 --> 07:54.823
- ♪ All the waiting, it's been hard ♪
- Okay.

07:54.824 --> 07:59.127
Well, you're...
Uh, g-give me the game.

08:01.881 --> 08:03.582
[ Sniffles ]

08:03.583 --> 08:07.135
Your daddy...
Your father...

08:07.136 --> 08:11.590
Was taken
by some bad men.

08:11.591 --> 08:14.376
And your grandpa Dan
got him back.

08:14.377 --> 08:16.377
Grandpa Dan saved dad?

08:16.378 --> 08:18.563
Yes.

08:20.483 --> 08:23.985
But he got...
He got really hurt doing it.

08:23.986 --> 08:26.154
He got hurt really badly.

08:26.155 --> 08:30.058
♪ For the rain to fall ♪

08:30.059 --> 08:32.177
He'll be okay.

08:32.178 --> 08:33.778
It's grandpa Dan.

08:36.832 --> 08:39.333
[ Monitor toeping ]

08:42.004 --> 08:43.270
Wow.

08:43.272 --> 08:44.756
Who died?

08:44.757 --> 08:47.876
This is all my fault.

08:47.877 --> 08:50.695
You got shot
because of me.

08:50.696 --> 08:53.698
Nathan...

08:53.699 --> 08:56.885
I made the decision
to go in there firing.

08:56.886 --> 08:59.588
And I'm the one
who took those men's lives.

08:59.589 --> 09:01.606
And I'd do it again.

09:01.607 --> 09:04.926
You didn't take
<i>all</i> their lives.

09:04.927 --> 09:06.194
I took one.

09:06.195 --> 09:08.446
I'm sorry I didn't
get you out of there

09:08.447 --> 09:09.966
before you had to do that.

09:11.400 --> 09:14.569
You were defending
yourself, son.

09:14.570 --> 09:16.288
We both know that.

09:16.289 --> 09:19.374
♪...Gather 'round
to celebrate ♪

09:19.375 --> 09:22.944
[ Sighs ] Look, uh...

09:22.945 --> 09:24.379
Some people
want to see you.

09:25.614 --> 09:28.233
Is it the cops?

09:28.234 --> 09:30.785
It's friends and family.

09:30.786 --> 09:33.421
I didn't know
I had either.

09:35.291 --> 09:36.758
[ Grunting ]

09:36.759 --> 09:38.176
Grandpa Dan?

09:41.297 --> 09:43.765
Hey, buddy.

09:43.766 --> 09:46.985
Sorry, I'm a little
out of it today.

09:46.986 --> 09:50.105
My mom says
you saved my dad.

09:50.106 --> 09:51.573
No.

09:51.574 --> 09:54.159
I just helped him
find his way home.

09:54.160 --> 09:56.811
She also said
you got pretty badly hurt.

09:56.812 --> 09:59.281
But she forgets
you're grandpa Dan.

09:59.282 --> 10:01.650
[ Chuckles lightly ]

10:01.651 --> 10:04.753
I'm sorry I yelled at you
the last time I saw you.

10:04.754 --> 10:08.790
You have nothing
to apologize for.

10:08.791 --> 10:11.826
When your father's gone,
you're the man of the house.

10:11.827 --> 10:14.596
That comes with
some tough decisions.

10:16.098 --> 10:18.633
I'm proud of the way
you handled yourself.

10:18.634 --> 10:22.837
So, are you gonna stay with us
when you get out of here?

10:22.838 --> 10:26.941
I don't think I'm gonna make it
this time, Jamie.

10:26.942 --> 10:29.611
You thought that last time
with your bad heart.

10:29.612 --> 10:30.695
You were fine.

10:30.696 --> 10:34.008
I think you'll be fine
this time, too.

10:40.656 --> 10:43.241
You have a son?

10:43.242 --> 10:44.943
Logan.

10:44.944 --> 10:46.861
How long have I
been gone?

10:46.862 --> 10:48.330
Six years, apparently.

10:48.331 --> 10:49.547
[ Chuckles ]

10:49.548 --> 10:51.032
How is it that
out of the two of us,

10:51.033 --> 10:52.533
I don't have
the most shocking news?

10:52.534 --> 10:55.303
Man, none of that
should have happened to you.

10:55.304 --> 10:56.471
It's my fault.

10:56.472 --> 10:58.857
I should have been the one
to go to Europe.

10:58.858 --> 11:00.525
No. No,
you shouldn't have.

11:00.526 --> 11:02.093
Dan wouldn't have come
to save you.

11:02.094 --> 11:03.345
He can't stand you.

11:03.346 --> 11:04.813
[ Both chuckle ]

11:04.814 --> 11:06.547
[ Sighs ]

11:06.548 --> 11:08.066
Dude,
you were kidnapped.

11:08.067 --> 11:09.818
Dude, you're a father.

11:09.819 --> 11:13.221
♪ Watching the pacific
from the sidelines ♪

11:13.222 --> 11:15.273
[ Sighs ]
I was kidnapped.

11:15.274 --> 11:16.908
♪ Wonder what it means
to live together ♪

11:16.909 --> 11:18.326
I'm a father.

11:18.327 --> 11:20.412
♪ Looking for more
than just guidelines ♪

11:20.413 --> 11:22.864
♪ looking for signs
in the night sky ♪

11:22.865 --> 11:25.066
Hey!

11:25.067 --> 11:26.418
Ohh!

11:26.419 --> 11:28.920
God, it's so good
to see you smile again.

11:28.921 --> 11:31.456
It's so good
to see Nathan.

11:31.457 --> 11:33.574
I couldn't have made it
through any of this

11:33.575 --> 11:35.543
without you, Quinn...
Thank you so much.

11:35.544 --> 11:37.629
We're family, Haley.
Of course.

11:37.630 --> 11:38.763
Yeah.
[ Exhales sharply ]

11:38.764 --> 11:41.015
Well, speaking of family,
<i>what?</i>

11:41.016 --> 11:43.251
Tell me about Logan.
What's he like?

11:43.252 --> 11:45.520
He's 6 years old,
and he is adorable.

11:45.521 --> 11:47.806
And, you know,
he's a little freaked out

11:47.807 --> 11:50.058
about Clay being
his father, but...

11:50.059 --> 11:51.192
He'll come around.

11:51.193 --> 11:53.561
He's obviously a tough kid.
It'll take time.

11:53.562 --> 11:54.863
It's got to be really hard

11:54.864 --> 11:57.198
growing up without a father,
you know?

11:57.199 --> 12:00.768
♪ I got my vice verses ♪

12:00.769 --> 12:02.120
Hey.

12:02.121 --> 12:04.572
Hey.

12:04.573 --> 12:08.243
Hey.
Congratulations, dad.

12:08.244 --> 12:09.627
Thanks.

12:11.297 --> 12:13.748
Oh, look at that.
[ Smooching ]

12:13.749 --> 12:16.617
I know you're probably wondering
how the line is coming.

12:16.618 --> 12:18.470
Ah, here we go.

12:18.471 --> 12:19.804
I've been a bit busy,

12:19.805 --> 12:22.140
what with the café
and the psychopath

12:22.141 --> 12:23.758
and my friend's
missing husband,

12:23.759 --> 12:27.312
<i>but</i> I have managed to sketch
a few rough samples.

12:27.313 --> 12:29.647
I have no doubt
they are top-notch,

12:29.648 --> 12:33.401
but I came to town because
I was concerned about you.

12:33.402 --> 12:36.104
So for now, no business.

12:36.105 --> 12:37.305
That sound okay?

12:37.306 --> 12:39.741
Sounds perfect.

12:39.742 --> 12:41.326
Good.

12:41.327 --> 12:43.244
♪ Everything seems
to fall apart ♪

12:43.245 --> 12:44.863
Haley.

12:44.864 --> 12:47.248
Haley, wake up.

12:47.249 --> 12:49.484
Look at Lydia... she's walking.
Come here.

12:49.485 --> 12:51.419
Mommy.
You can do it.

12:51.420 --> 12:52.787
Oh.

12:52.788 --> 12:55.990
Mommy. Mommy.
Good girl. Good girl.

12:55.991 --> 12:57.709
Mommy.
Nathan: Yeah!

12:57.710 --> 13:01.045
♪ A little resurrection
every time I fall ♪

13:01.046 --> 13:03.498
Hey. Hey, hey, hey.
What's wrong?

13:03.499 --> 13:06.000
♪ You've got your babies,
I got my hearses ♪

13:06.001 --> 13:07.769
[ Crying ]
I've just been trying

13:07.770 --> 13:09.971
to hold it all together
for so long.

13:09.972 --> 13:11.856
It's just [Sniffles]
she started...

13:11.857 --> 13:14.142
She started walking
when you were gone,

13:14.143 --> 13:17.028
and [Sobs]
I just started thinking,

13:17.029 --> 13:19.113
what if you
never came home?

13:19.114 --> 13:20.198
And what would I do?

13:20.199 --> 13:21.849
I don't know how I would live
without you,

13:21.850 --> 13:23.067
how I would go on.

13:23.068 --> 13:25.987
I can't wake up every morning
without you next to me,

13:25.988 --> 13:27.188
and I can't imagine it.
Okay, okay.

13:27.189 --> 13:30.742
♪ And I got my vice verses ♪

13:30.743 --> 13:32.627
Hey, hey.

13:32.628 --> 13:36.331
You know what I kept imagining
the whole time I was kidnapped?

13:36.332 --> 13:39.751
Opening up the door to our home
and seeing you.

13:39.752 --> 13:43.805
It's what kept me going...
The thought of us together.

13:43.806 --> 13:46.841
It's all we ever need
to think about.

13:46.842 --> 13:49.227
[ Babbling ]

13:49.228 --> 13:50.979
Mommy?

14:09.841 --> 14:14.378
♪ Where did you go now ♪

14:14.379 --> 14:17.264
♪ and where have you been ♪

14:17.265 --> 14:19.934
♪ all day long ♪

14:19.935 --> 14:22.853
♪ as I sit here waiting? ♪

14:22.854 --> 14:24.755
All right. Whatcha gonna do
about that, huh?

14:24.756 --> 14:26.140
Big mistake.

14:26.141 --> 14:27.641
What?!

14:27.642 --> 14:28.743
Oh-ho-ho!

14:28.744 --> 14:29.777
Are you serious?

14:29.778 --> 14:32.229
When did you get so good
at this game?

14:32.230 --> 14:33.998
You been playing
with mom?

14:33.999 --> 14:36.283
Everything
looks so good...

14:36.284 --> 14:38.219
Except that.

14:38.220 --> 14:39.954
That looks
a little too much

14:39.955 --> 14:41.789
like what came out
of Jude today.

14:41.790 --> 14:44.175
He does that all the time,
you know?

14:44.176 --> 14:45.960
He's probably doing it
right now.

14:45.961 --> 14:48.112
Hey, hey.

14:48.113 --> 14:49.497
Brooke and I
had a fantastic day.

14:49.498 --> 14:52.099
How about you, Julian?

14:52.100 --> 14:54.969
I think I finally found
a project for my sound stage.

14:54.970 --> 14:57.304
I've been reading
"an unkindness of ravens" again.

14:57.305 --> 14:58.455
I really love that story.

14:58.456 --> 14:59.840
Well, of course you do.

14:59.841 --> 15:02.643
It's the book that made you
fall in love with <i>me.</i>

15:02.644 --> 15:04.678
[ Laughs ]
The scope of the story

15:04.679 --> 15:06.072
just seems so much bigger
than a movie.

15:06.073 --> 15:08.241
Maybe it could be
a TV show.

15:08.242 --> 15:10.134
I always liked that book.

15:10.135 --> 15:11.635
You read that book?

15:11.636 --> 15:13.287
[ Glasses clink ]
Of course I did.

15:13.288 --> 15:14.956
It was about
my little girl.

15:14.957 --> 15:16.157
It got some things wrong.

15:16.158 --> 15:18.159
New York wasn't
your first fashion show.

15:18.160 --> 15:20.461
You had that in our living room
when you were 8.

15:20.462 --> 15:22.163
She dressed up all her dolls,

15:22.164 --> 15:23.631
then when those ran out,

15:23.632 --> 15:25.299
she started
putting clothes

15:25.300 --> 15:27.385
on every piece of furniture
in the house.

15:27.386 --> 15:30.721
I... cannot believe
you remember that.

15:30.722 --> 15:33.424
I stretched mom's favorite dress
over a lamp.

15:33.425 --> 15:34.658
She got <i>so</i> mad.

15:34.659 --> 15:37.178
Only because it looked better
than her.

15:37.179 --> 15:39.680
[ Brooke and Julian laugh ]
[ Cellphone rings ]

15:39.681 --> 15:41.465
Excuse me.

15:41.466 --> 15:43.568
[ Cellphone beeps ]

15:43.569 --> 15:46.904
It seems like you two
are having fun.

15:46.905 --> 15:48.055
<i>So</i> much fun.

15:48.056 --> 15:51.275
I couldn't have asked
for a better day.

15:51.276 --> 15:55.396
Haley has Nathan back,
my husband is inspired, and...

15:55.397 --> 15:59.349
It feels like I finally have
the father I always wanted.

15:59.350 --> 16:02.119
It's literally been...

16:02.120 --> 16:06.132
Too good to be true.

16:06.133 --> 16:08.025
I know you told me
to stay away,

16:08.026 --> 16:10.244
but I've already been away
for too long.

16:10.245 --> 16:12.496
Look, I-I don't just remember
Logan, Sam.

16:12.497 --> 16:13.798
I remember wanting him.

16:13.799 --> 16:16.333
I remember bringing him home
from the hospital

16:16.334 --> 16:18.352
and how happy we were
to have a son.

16:18.353 --> 16:21.022
And now that I remember,
it's impossible to imagine

16:21.023 --> 16:22.306
how I ever forgot.

16:22.307 --> 16:25.042
But I did because
of how much I love Sara.

16:25.043 --> 16:28.229
But I'm here now because
of how much I love Logan.

16:28.230 --> 16:29.880
Look...

16:29.881 --> 16:31.715
I once proved to you
that I was worthy enough

16:31.716 --> 16:32.883
to marry your daughter,

16:32.884 --> 16:34.185
and I'm gonna prove to you

16:34.186 --> 16:36.270
that I can be a good father
to Logan.

16:36.271 --> 16:39.156
I know that he's all
you have left of Sara.

16:39.157 --> 16:42.276
But he's all that I have left
of her, too.

16:48.083 --> 16:50.718
I've got an idea.

16:50.719 --> 16:53.254
How about tomorrow night,
I cook dinner for you two?

16:53.255 --> 16:55.206
We'll throw some steaks
on the grill.

16:55.207 --> 16:56.849
Sounds good.

16:56.850 --> 16:58.843
Thanks, daddy.

16:58.844 --> 17:00.044
I have to ask,

17:00.045 --> 17:04.431
did you really come to town
just to spend time with me?

17:04.432 --> 17:06.525
There's no other reason?

17:08.252 --> 17:09.720
[ Laughs ]

17:09.721 --> 17:13.089
Okay, you caught me. Yeah.
I have some great news.

17:13.090 --> 17:15.826
We have an offer
to sell Baker man.

17:15.827 --> 17:17.426
Sell it?

17:17.428 --> 17:19.113
It... doesn't even
exist yet.

17:19.114 --> 17:21.082
That's why
it's such great news.

17:21.083 --> 17:23.284
A large chain is willing
to pay a fortune

17:23.285 --> 17:24.710
just for your name and idea.

17:24.711 --> 17:27.713
[ Exhales sharply ]

17:27.714 --> 17:30.299
Of course,
the final decision is up to you.

17:34.946 --> 17:36.514
So, what do you think?

17:36.515 --> 17:39.183
I think I need to go check
on the boys.

17:40.585 --> 17:42.353
Excuse me.

17:42.354 --> 17:44.939
Do you have any queens?

17:44.940 --> 17:46.190
Nope. Go fish.

17:46.191 --> 17:49.426
So I guess it must've been
pretty tough for you

17:49.427 --> 17:50.861
when I was gone, huh?

17:50.862 --> 17:53.480
Yeah. Being the man of the house
isn't easy.

17:53.481 --> 17:56.075
No, sometimes it isn't.

17:56.076 --> 17:57.318
You know what's cool?

17:57.319 --> 17:58.736
We've both been kidnapped,

17:58.737 --> 18:00.137
and grandpa Dan
saved both of us.

18:00.138 --> 18:02.339
Yeah.

18:02.340 --> 18:05.676
I guess
that <i>is</i> pretty cool.

18:05.677 --> 18:08.087
Now that you two
are getting along,

18:08.088 --> 18:09.588
can we all go camping
when he gets out?

18:09.589 --> 18:11.148
[ Sighs ]

18:11.149 --> 18:14.919
Grandpa Dan isn't getting out of
the hospital this time, Jamie.

18:16.171 --> 18:18.289
He'll be all right.
He's grandpa Dan.

18:18.290 --> 18:20.307
You always say
Scott men are tough.

18:20.308 --> 18:24.428
They are.
He's the toughest guy I know.

18:24.429 --> 18:27.189
But he's dying, Jamie.

18:29.851 --> 18:32.236
Right now, he needs you
to be tough for him.

18:34.472 --> 18:36.857
Did you tell Lydia yet?

18:36.858 --> 18:38.943
No, I didn't.

18:41.346 --> 18:42.830
I'll tell her.

18:42.831 --> 18:46.533
She'll take it better
coming from me.

18:48.186 --> 18:49.903
Told you
Scott men were tough.

18:49.904 --> 18:52.856
You can't kill Dan Scott!

18:52.857 --> 18:54.708
You could get yourself killed
out here.

18:54.709 --> 18:56.844
[ Tires screech ]

18:56.845 --> 18:58.179
[ Horn blares ]

19:01.883 --> 19:03.533
[ Monitor beeping ]

19:03.534 --> 19:05.019
Hey.

19:05.020 --> 19:07.204
Hi.

19:08.890 --> 19:10.900
Hi, Lydia.

19:14.379 --> 19:16.280
I talked with Lucas.

19:16.281 --> 19:18.649
He's not coming.

19:18.650 --> 19:20.250
I'm sorry.

19:20.251 --> 19:22.536
[ Sighs ]

19:22.537 --> 19:26.140
Well, I wasn't there
for <i>his</i> life.

19:26.141 --> 19:29.076
Can't expect him to be here
while I'm dying.

19:29.077 --> 19:31.462
♪ And we can't get back up ♪

19:31.463 --> 19:34.114
Besides...

19:34.115 --> 19:37.968
I robbed him of the only father
he ever knew.

19:37.969 --> 19:42.181
Haley,
I never apologized to you.

19:42.182 --> 19:45.075
Keith was a big part
of your life.

19:45.076 --> 19:47.853
And I took him
from you, too.

19:47.854 --> 19:50.189
♪ Goodbye, goodbye, goodbye ♪

19:50.190 --> 19:52.850
Haley...

19:52.851 --> 19:55.277
I'm so sorry.

19:59.190 --> 20:03.744
I can't thank you enough
for bringing Nathan home.

20:03.745 --> 20:06.038
I couldn't have done it
without you.

20:09.267 --> 20:11.877
You know,
I used to think

20:11.878 --> 20:13.587
no one was ever good enough
for my son.

20:13.588 --> 20:17.157
♪ I took you for granted ♪

20:17.158 --> 20:20.961
But I am so happy
to be proven wrong.

20:20.962 --> 20:24.098
He's the best thing
that ever happened to me,

20:24.099 --> 20:27.968
and you're the best thing
that ever happened to him.

20:27.969 --> 20:31.955
♪...Looking back again ♪

20:31.956 --> 20:33.974
[ Cries, sniffles ]

20:33.975 --> 20:36.293
Would you like
to hold Lydia?

20:36.294 --> 20:38.028
I would.

20:38.029 --> 20:40.698
♪ 'Cause we never
understand... ♪

20:40.699 --> 20:42.408
Yeah.

20:42.409 --> 20:46.303
Want to go say hi?

20:46.304 --> 20:48.414
Say hi.

20:48.415 --> 20:51.625
♪ Goodbye, goodbye, goodbye ♪

20:51.626 --> 20:53.944
♪ goodbye, goodbye, goodbye ♪

20:53.945 --> 20:56.881
It's too bad
she'll never get to know me.

20:59.400 --> 21:03.287
Then again,
maybe that's a good thing.

21:03.288 --> 21:05.139
♪ Goodbye, goodbye, goodbye ♪

21:05.140 --> 21:08.175
♪ goodbye, goodbye, goodbye ♪

21:11.045 --> 21:14.264
I know I'm supposed
to be tough.

21:14.265 --> 21:16.442
I don't want you to go.

21:16.443 --> 21:19.553
♪ And I don't know how ♪

21:19.554 --> 21:22.114
♪ but I know I'll see ♪

21:22.115 --> 21:25.675
♪ your face somehow ♪

21:25.676 --> 21:27.978
It's okay, buddy.

21:27.979 --> 21:31.131
I'm not feeling that tough
right now, either.

21:31.132 --> 21:33.283
♪ It'll be all right ♪

21:33.284 --> 21:38.071
When Lydia asks about
her grandpa Dan [Sniffles]

21:38.072 --> 21:43.844
We will tell her how much
he loved his grandchildren.

21:49.934 --> 21:54.254
♪ Goodbye, goodbye,
goodbye, goodbye ♪

21:54.255 --> 21:57.674
♪ goodbye, goodbye,
goodbye, goodbye ♪

22:02.814 --> 22:06.266
♪ goodbye, goodbye,
goodbye, goodbye ♪

22:15.088 --> 22:16.505
Hey.

22:18.091 --> 22:20.009
I brought you something.

22:22.012 --> 22:24.797
Cool... an airplane!

22:24.798 --> 22:27.333
No, not just any airplane.
That's the x-jet.

22:27.334 --> 22:29.802
That's what Wolverine
and his friends use.

22:31.355 --> 22:33.005
[ Box thuds ]

22:36.276 --> 22:39.678
I don't blame you
for being mad at me.

22:39.679 --> 22:42.027
I'm mad at me, too.

22:42.028 --> 22:43.316
I'm mad that I left,

22:43.317 --> 22:45.051
and I'm mad that it took me
so long to come back.

22:45.052 --> 22:48.270
Then why didn't you?

22:48.271 --> 22:51.457
Well, when your mom went away,
I got sick.

22:51.458 --> 22:54.627
But Dr. Alvarez
helped me get better,

22:54.628 --> 22:57.613
and now I'm here
to make it up to you.

22:57.614 --> 23:00.295
Did you love my mommy?

23:00.296 --> 23:03.469
More than anything
in the world.

23:09.760 --> 23:11.811
Okay, I'm gonna go, but...

23:11.812 --> 23:15.314
I'd like to come back
and see you more often.

23:15.315 --> 23:17.149
I hope that'll be okay.

23:23.857 --> 23:27.193
What if you
wander away again?

23:27.194 --> 23:30.896
Well, I <i>wasn't</i> wandering away.
I was looking for something.

23:30.897 --> 23:33.616
And I found
what I was looking for...

23:33.617 --> 23:35.284
You.

23:45.429 --> 23:48.931
[ Baby cooing ]

23:48.932 --> 23:50.416
[ Knock on door ]

23:52.269 --> 23:53.686
You okay?

23:53.687 --> 23:55.688
Yeah.
Why wouldn't I be?

23:55.689 --> 23:58.691
I took an idea
and a few sketches to my dad,

23:58.692 --> 24:02.895
and he's already turned it
into potentially a huge profit.

24:02.896 --> 24:04.563
He's a great
businessman.

24:04.564 --> 24:07.283
[ Scoffs ] Maybe,
but he's a horrible father.

24:07.284 --> 24:09.735
You didn't bring
Baker man to him

24:09.736 --> 24:11.237
because he's a good
businessman.

24:11.238 --> 24:13.122
You brought it to him
because he's your dad

24:13.123 --> 24:14.790
and you wanted a relationship
with him.

24:16.793 --> 24:18.711
You get it,

24:18.712 --> 24:20.913
so why doesn't he?

24:20.914 --> 24:22.164
Well,
my dad didn't, either,

24:22.165 --> 24:23.799
until I gave him a push
in the right direction.

24:25.585 --> 24:26.969
Maybe that's what
your dad needs.

24:29.973 --> 24:31.557
So try telling him
exactly how you feel.

24:39.649 --> 24:42.268
[ Monitor beeping ]

24:42.269 --> 24:44.520
Am I in hell?

24:44.521 --> 24:45.855
[ Chuckles softly ]

24:45.856 --> 24:47.653
Not yet.

24:49.276 --> 24:52.111
But it's good to see you still
have your sense of humor.

24:52.112 --> 24:53.996
How many times
have you dreamed

24:53.997 --> 24:55.948
about standing over
my deathbed?

24:55.949 --> 24:59.502
Mm, well, actually, I kind of
thought you'd outlive us all

24:59.503 --> 25:01.620
and end up dancing
on <i>my</i> grave.

25:01.621 --> 25:04.623
That <i>was</i> the plan.
[ Chuckles ]

25:04.624 --> 25:07.710
♪ But I'm here to tell you ♪

25:10.964 --> 25:13.332
You did a good thing, Dan.

25:13.333 --> 25:16.635
Our son is alive
because of you.

25:16.636 --> 25:21.874
Nothing on this earth could stop
me from bringing him home.

25:21.875 --> 25:24.844
Besides...

25:24.845 --> 25:29.198
I've done enough awful things
in this life.

25:29.199 --> 25:31.150
I think I was due.

25:34.070 --> 25:36.989
Is there anything
you need?

25:36.990 --> 25:39.058
Yeah.

25:39.059 --> 25:42.661
I need you to stop blaming
yourself for Keith's death.

25:42.662 --> 25:46.048
I know you carry the guilt
around with you,

25:46.049 --> 25:48.083
but it's not your fault.

25:48.084 --> 25:52.071
I took his life.
Just me.

25:52.072 --> 25:54.473
You had no part in it.

25:57.394 --> 26:00.679
♪ Nobody knows ♪

26:00.680 --> 26:01.814
Deb.

26:03.383 --> 26:05.618
So...

26:05.619 --> 26:07.102
How about one more...

26:07.103 --> 26:08.354
[ Laughs ]

26:08.355 --> 26:09.438
... for old time's sake?

26:09.439 --> 26:11.774
Of course,
you'll have to do all the work.

26:11.775 --> 26:13.572
Oh, as usual.

26:16.696 --> 26:19.949
♪ Changes ♪

26:19.950 --> 26:22.785
♪ all of these changes ♪

26:22.786 --> 26:24.920
[ Sighs ]

26:24.921 --> 26:27.239
I spent so much time
hating him.

26:27.240 --> 26:30.509
He didn't give you much reason
to love him.

26:33.597 --> 26:35.581
How can you be so strong?

26:35.582 --> 26:39.051
I mean, I've never lost anyone
the way that you have...

26:39.052 --> 26:41.270
Your mom, your dad.

26:41.271 --> 26:42.754
How did you do it?

26:42.755 --> 26:46.592
With you and Jamie...

26:46.593 --> 26:49.778
And our friends.

26:52.782 --> 26:54.366
I'm here for you.

26:54.367 --> 26:56.619
And they are, too.

26:56.620 --> 27:00.239
Yeah, but that's just it.
I never thought I needed it.

27:00.240 --> 27:02.041
I was never close
with my parents

27:02.042 --> 27:03.775
the way that you were
with yours, you know?

27:03.776 --> 27:06.045
And now that Dan is dying,
I just...

27:06.046 --> 27:07.279
All I can think about

27:07.280 --> 27:09.582
is how much time I've wasted
just hating him.

27:09.583 --> 27:11.834
You had a good reason.
You were trying to protect your family.

27:11.835 --> 27:13.669
Why do I feel so bad?

27:13.670 --> 27:16.255
Because you are
a good man.

27:16.256 --> 27:19.625
You're one of the best I know,
Nathan Scott.

27:19.626 --> 27:20.843
[ Sighs ]

27:25.065 --> 27:27.933
I don't feel like
a good man.

27:27.934 --> 27:31.236
One of the good things
about my mom finding out

27:31.237 --> 27:34.023
that she only had
a little time left...

27:34.024 --> 27:37.192
Was that we got to say goodbye
to each other.

27:39.412 --> 27:42.948
It really helped
to have that closure.

27:44.784 --> 27:47.453
Maybe that's what
you need.

27:51.257 --> 27:54.877
You two deciding what to do
with all your new money?

27:57.664 --> 28:00.132
I don't want to sell
the company.

28:00.133 --> 28:01.833
[ Papers rustle ]

28:01.834 --> 28:04.353
May I ask why?

28:04.354 --> 28:08.006
Because I already had to sell
clothes over bros,

28:08.007 --> 28:11.393
and I want to have something
of my own again.

28:11.394 --> 28:14.846
You said yourself that the line
doesn't even exist yet.

28:14.847 --> 28:17.800
That's why it makes
such good sense to sell it.

28:17.801 --> 28:19.618
That's not the point,
daddy.

28:19.619 --> 28:22.854
The point of this was for us
to do something together.

28:22.855 --> 28:24.540
And we did that.

28:24.541 --> 28:26.458
But it's a business.

28:26.459 --> 28:30.329
And the smart business move
is to sell.

28:30.330 --> 28:33.699
I'm sorry, daddy,
but my answer is no.

28:33.700 --> 28:35.000
Don't be foolish.

28:35.001 --> 28:37.753
I've already put together
the paperwork for you.

28:37.754 --> 28:40.305
[ Scoffs ]

28:40.306 --> 28:43.475
I thought that you said
the final decision in this

28:43.476 --> 28:44.765
was up to <i>me.</i>

28:44.766 --> 28:46.095
It is.

28:46.096 --> 28:48.681
I just expected that
you'd make the right one.

28:48.682 --> 28:50.983
You knew
I wouldn't want to sell.

28:50.984 --> 28:54.319
And that's the whole reason
that you flew down here.

28:54.320 --> 28:57.189
It wasn't to check on me

28:57.190 --> 28:59.057
or spend time
with your little girl.

28:59.058 --> 29:01.276
You came here
to put on a show.

29:01.277 --> 29:03.696
[ Chuckles ]
What show?

29:03.697 --> 29:05.063
Playing with my boys

29:05.064 --> 29:08.417
and this whole father/daughter
"let's not talk business" day,

29:08.418 --> 29:11.003
dinner, stories about me
when I was a kid.

29:11.004 --> 29:12.709
I can't believe it.

29:12.710 --> 29:16.458
I'm just another client to you,
another deal you had to close.

29:16.459 --> 29:18.840
Brooke, don't be ridiculous.
You're over-reacting.

29:18.841 --> 29:19.911
No.

29:19.912 --> 29:22.014
Julian thought
that you could use a push

29:22.015 --> 29:23.382
in the right direction.

29:23.383 --> 29:25.551
How's this?
Get out!

29:25.552 --> 29:27.586
Brooke...
Go!

29:27.587 --> 29:29.104
I want you out of here.

29:29.105 --> 29:31.356
I cannot believe
I am such a sucker.

29:31.357 --> 29:33.809
You want Baker man?
Fine, take it.

29:33.810 --> 29:35.811
I do not want
any part of it!

29:35.812 --> 29:38.030
Y-you're acting
like a child.

29:38.031 --> 29:39.648
How would you know?

29:39.649 --> 29:42.534
You weren't around
when I was a child.

29:43.787 --> 29:45.287
Get out!

29:46.873 --> 29:49.908
Congratulations, daddy.
You closed the deal.

29:49.909 --> 29:52.027
Guess what...
I can close things, too.

30:08.422 --> 30:11.017
Logan, this is Quinn.

30:12.843 --> 30:14.460
Hi, Logan.

30:14.461 --> 30:16.295
Hi.

30:16.296 --> 30:20.015
Quinn,
this is Logan, my son.

30:20.016 --> 30:22.946
It's nice to meet you.

30:36.116 --> 30:38.951
I like the cargo pockets
on the shorts.

30:38.952 --> 30:40.119
[ Chuckles ]

30:40.120 --> 30:42.721
Kids should have to carry
their own diapers.

30:44.658 --> 30:48.077
He tricked me.

30:48.078 --> 30:52.181
I fell for his charm,
like I always do, and...

30:52.182 --> 30:56.051
He left me
like he always does.

30:56.052 --> 30:57.887
He just doesn't <i>know</i> you.

30:57.888 --> 31:01.023
If he would spend
one real second with you,

31:01.024 --> 31:04.843
he would know that you're
the most caring, most loving,

31:04.844 --> 31:07.446
most amazing person
in the world.

31:08.865 --> 31:11.534
[ Voice breaking ] If you make
the "ravens" TV show,

31:11.535 --> 31:13.953
can you make him get hit
by a bus or something?

31:13.954 --> 31:15.387
[ Chuckles ]

31:15.388 --> 31:18.090
I'll probably
just leave him out.

31:18.091 --> 31:21.127
A character who doesn't love
Brooke Davis...

31:21.128 --> 31:22.528
[ Sniffles ]

31:22.529 --> 31:25.030
... I wouldn't even know how
to write that.

31:27.667 --> 31:29.218
Hey.
[ Sniffles ]

31:32.422 --> 31:36.859
Why doesn't my dad
want me?

31:36.860 --> 31:40.095
[ Sniffles ]

31:40.096 --> 31:43.443
Dad.

31:43.444 --> 31:45.351
Dad?

31:45.352 --> 31:48.720
Why does this
have to be so difficult?

31:48.721 --> 31:52.658
You're my father,
so I should love you, but...

31:52.659 --> 31:56.178
I've spent so much of my life
hating you.

31:56.179 --> 31:59.949
I was a terrible father.
I know that.

31:59.950 --> 32:01.667
You know, I can justify

32:01.668 --> 32:05.054
a lot of the screwed-up things
that you've done.

32:05.055 --> 32:08.624
You bullied me because you
wanted to make me tough.

32:08.625 --> 32:11.544
You tried to ruin
my marriage

32:11.545 --> 32:13.879
because you wanted me
to have a career.

32:13.880 --> 32:16.098
You even burned down
your diner

32:16.099 --> 32:19.185
just because you wanted
to see me again.

32:19.186 --> 32:22.071
But I <i>can't</i> understand

32:22.072 --> 32:24.776
how you could murder
your own brother.

32:27.227 --> 32:28.277
And I'm worried.

32:28.278 --> 32:30.479
I'm worried
that when you're gone,

32:30.480 --> 32:32.031
that's all I'll remember.

32:33.867 --> 32:36.952
And I'll still
hate you for it.

32:36.953 --> 32:39.905
You <i>should
hate me for it.</i>

32:39.906 --> 32:42.502
So why did you do it?

32:44.995 --> 32:47.796
I was <i>always</i> jealous
of Keith,

32:47.797 --> 32:50.416
even when we were kids.

32:50.417 --> 32:54.920
I was athletic, popular,
all the things that he wasn't.

32:54.921 --> 32:58.574
But still,
I was jealous of him.

32:58.575 --> 33:02.461
People were drawn to Keith,
and I hated him for it.

33:02.462 --> 33:05.097
So you shot him
because people liked him more?

33:05.098 --> 33:09.151
The day I shot Keith,
I was in a dark place.

33:09.152 --> 33:12.971
I was convinced
that he tried to kill me.

33:12.972 --> 33:15.952
I'd lost you,
divorced your mom.

33:15.953 --> 33:17.443
My life was
spiraling downwards,

33:17.444 --> 33:19.328
and meanwhile,
Keith was building a new life

33:19.329 --> 33:20.696
with my
high-school sweetheart

33:20.697 --> 33:22.114
and the child
that I abandoned.

33:22.115 --> 33:23.365
Every time
I looked at him,

33:23.366 --> 33:24.983
I felt like I was punched
in the gut.

33:24.984 --> 33:27.964
So what happened
in that hallway?

33:30.123 --> 33:33.926
Keith wanted to go into
the school to save that kid.

33:33.927 --> 33:36.128
So I let him go...

33:36.129 --> 33:38.547
Hoping he'd get shot.

33:38.548 --> 33:40.215
Let him be the hero...

33:40.216 --> 33:43.385
As long as he was
a dead hero.

33:43.386 --> 33:46.355
And then I thought...

33:46.356 --> 33:50.509
"Why should <i>he</i> be the hero
when it could be <i>me?"</i>

33:50.510 --> 33:52.444
So I followed him in.

33:54.881 --> 33:56.865
Jimmy was crying.

33:56.866 --> 34:00.235
And Keith
was telling him,

34:00.236 --> 34:02.154
"it gets better.

34:02.155 --> 34:03.455
"That pain in your heart,

34:03.456 --> 34:04.690
"that voice in your head

34:04.691 --> 34:06.508
"that tells you
there's no way out...

34:06.509 --> 34:08.077
"It's wrong.

34:08.078 --> 34:10.346
It gets better."

34:10.347 --> 34:13.677
And I felt like
he was talking to me.

34:13.678 --> 34:15.884
And in that moment,

34:15.885 --> 34:19.838
maybe...
The most heroic...

34:19.839 --> 34:23.542
Kindest moment
of my big brother's life...

34:23.543 --> 34:25.777
I hated him.

34:25.779 --> 34:28.647
I hated him more than anyone
or anything,

34:28.648 --> 34:31.516
because <i>nothing
had gotten better.</i>

34:33.402 --> 34:36.021
That pain was still
in my heart.

34:36.022 --> 34:37.889
That voice in my head

34:37.889 --> 34:41.443
saying that there's no way out
was right!

34:41.444 --> 34:44.496
And he was standing there,
lying to me.

34:44.496 --> 34:48.734
And after Jimmy died,

34:48.735 --> 34:52.254
I picked up the gun,
and I aimed it at Keith.

34:52.255 --> 34:54.540
And he looked at me.

34:54.541 --> 34:56.925
And all I could think of

34:56.926 --> 34:59.128
was how everything
that had gone wrong

34:59.129 --> 35:02.181
in my life was his fault...

35:02.182 --> 35:06.135
And it wasn't gonna get better
until he was gone.

35:07.887 --> 35:11.757
Just pull the trigger,
and it all ends.

35:14.444 --> 35:18.530
[ Voice breaking ]
So I pulled that trigger.

35:18.531 --> 35:20.199
And it <i>didn't</i> end.

35:22.569 --> 35:24.620
It got worse.

35:33.279 --> 35:35.714
I'm so sorry.

35:35.715 --> 35:38.250
[ Crying ]
I'm so sorry.

35:38.251 --> 35:40.263
I'm so sorry.

35:43.923 --> 35:49.922
♪ I believe in times passing ♪

35:50.814 --> 35:53.465
There are a lot of people
that you need to say

35:53.466 --> 35:55.067
"I'm sorry" to.

35:55.068 --> 35:56.985
[ Sighs ]

35:56.986 --> 35:59.571
But I'm not one of them.

35:59.572 --> 36:03.192
I wouldn't be where I am
if it wasn't for you...

36:03.193 --> 36:05.477
My career, my family...

36:05.478 --> 36:07.062
My life.

36:09.616 --> 36:12.668
No matter what you've done,
you're still my father.

36:15.822 --> 36:19.241
You're my father,
and I love you.

36:19.242 --> 36:23.629
Oh, Nathan...

36:23.630 --> 36:27.332
I love you, too.

36:27.333 --> 36:33.332
♪ I believe ♪

36:39.529 --> 36:42.614
You know...

36:42.615 --> 36:44.950
We never got a chance to play
a game together

36:44.951 --> 36:47.853
on the rivercourt.
How about it?

36:47.854 --> 36:49.955
[ Chuckles ]

36:49.956 --> 36:52.085
What do you want
to play to?

36:54.360 --> 36:56.361
Let's not keep score.

36:56.362 --> 36:59.801
For once,
let's just play to play.

37:28.695 --> 37:33.165
[ Monitor beeping ]
Dad?

37:33.166 --> 37:34.700
♪ I believe... ♪

37:34.701 --> 37:35.884
Dad.

37:35.885 --> 37:38.236
Dad?

37:38.237 --> 37:40.706
Dad, hey.
Hey!

37:40.707 --> 37:42.407
[ Beeping continues ]

37:42.408 --> 37:44.576
Dad, come on.

37:44.577 --> 37:45.928
[ Flatlining ]

38:05.198 --> 38:07.265
Keith.

38:07.266 --> 38:09.368
Hi, Danny.

38:09.369 --> 38:13.438
♪ Oh, morning come bursting,
the clouds ♪

38:13.439 --> 38:15.106
♪ amen ♪

38:15.107 --> 38:18.443
♪ lift off this blindfold ♪

38:18.444 --> 38:22.080
♪ let me see again ♪

38:22.081 --> 38:24.800
♪ and bring back the water ♪

38:24.801 --> 38:28.053
♪ let your ships roll in ♪

38:28.054 --> 38:30.789
♪ in my heart, she... ♪

38:30.790 --> 38:33.625
What are we doing
back here, Keith?

38:33.626 --> 38:37.440
I don't think either one of us
ever really left, Danny.

38:39.265 --> 38:41.800
Keith...

38:41.801 --> 38:43.936
If I could take it back...

38:43.937 --> 38:47.639
Well, you can't.
I think we both know that.

38:47.640 --> 38:49.825
I'm so sorry...

38:49.826 --> 38:52.978
For that day and every day
before it.

38:52.979 --> 38:55.347
I know you are, Danny.

38:55.348 --> 38:57.315
And I forgive you.

38:57.316 --> 38:59.034
I took you away from everyone
and everything

38:59.035 --> 39:00.953
you ever cared about...
How can you just forgive me?

39:00.954 --> 39:02.454
Well, you're dead, Dan.

39:02.455 --> 39:04.957
If I can't forgive you now,
when can I?

39:04.958 --> 39:06.157
[ Chuckles softly ]

39:07.760 --> 39:10.712
Look, Danny, you've done
some horrific things.

39:10.713 --> 39:13.893
You can't change that,
and you can't take it back.

39:13.894 --> 39:15.467
Since then, you've done
everything you could

39:15.468 --> 39:16.668
to make up for it.

39:16.669 --> 39:17.939
You've become
a better man.

39:17.940 --> 39:19.888
[ Scoffs ]

39:19.889 --> 39:22.240
I lied about
my heart transplant.

39:22.241 --> 39:24.309
My book and show
were a fraud.

39:24.310 --> 39:25.978
I set my own diner
on fire.

39:25.979 --> 39:28.783
Well, I didn't say
you were perfect.

39:28.784 --> 39:30.999
But nobody is.

39:31.000 --> 39:32.818
But you learned
what's important.

39:32.819 --> 39:35.654
You learned to put friends
and family first.

39:35.655 --> 39:37.990
And you've become
the selfless, kind person

39:37.991 --> 39:40.191
that I always wanted
for a brother.

39:40.192 --> 39:42.088
Like the kind of brother
you were.

39:43.946 --> 39:48.333
For so many years,
I was so jealous of you.

39:48.334 --> 39:50.419
♪ Don't let go ♪

39:50.420 --> 39:53.555
I should've been trying
to be more like you.

39:53.556 --> 39:55.874
I should've been proud
of you.

39:55.875 --> 39:59.394
♪ Fly up to the surface
and just start again ♪

39:59.395 --> 40:01.212
I am proud of you.

40:03.483 --> 40:06.134
I love you, Keith.

40:07.570 --> 40:11.440
♪ Just erodes us in the rain ♪

40:11.441 --> 40:14.159
I love you, too, Danny.

40:14.160 --> 40:16.061
♪...Erodes us in the rain ♪

40:16.062 --> 40:18.080
♪ sing ♪

40:19.899 --> 40:22.067
Come on.

40:22.068 --> 40:25.620
♪ Sl-o-o-o-ow it down ♪

40:30.209 --> 40:36.208
♪ sl-o-o-o-ow it down ♪

40:52.765 --> 40:55.634
I told you
the voice was wrong.

40:55.635 --> 40:57.288
It gets better.

41:04.460 --> 41:06.378
Come on, little brother.

41:06.379 --> 41:07.963
Take a walk with me.

41:10.133 --> 41:14.219
♪ Through chaos as it swirls ♪

41:14.220 --> 41:16.454
I know where <i>you're</i> going.

41:16.455 --> 41:18.289
But what about me?

41:18.290 --> 41:22.811
Don't worry, little brother.
You're my "plus one."

41:22.812 --> 41:28.811
♪ Through chaos as it swirls ♪

41:29.652 --> 41:33.155
♪ it's us against the world ♪

